":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1357051,"age":70,"year":"1495","julianDay":2267098,"description":"Russians forces invade Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1702078,"age":70,"year":"1495","toYear":"1497","julianDay":2267098,"title":"The Russo-Swedish War","description":"While in an alliance with Grand Prince Ivan III of Moscow, King Hans of Denmark and Norway invaded Sweden and was declared King of Sweden.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russo-Swedish_War_(1495%E2%80%931497)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Swedish War","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Ragnhild Gustafsdotter Gumsehuvud was born in 1425, in Västra Götaland, Sweden, her father, Gustav Ragnvaldsson Gumsehufvud Näf, was 20 and her mother, Birgitta Olofsdotter, was 25. She had at least 1 daughter with Bengt Andersson Öra. She died in 1514, in Råda, Skaraborg, Sweden, at the age of 89."},"et":{"1425–1514":"1425–1514","1420–1473":"1420–1473","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1400–1425":"1400–1425","BEF 15 AUG 1422":"enne 15. augustit 1422","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1514":"1514","1425":"1425","1436":"1436","1400":"1400","1497":"1497","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1485":"1485","1405":"1405","Västra Götaland, Sverige":"Västra Götaland, Rootsi","Byrsta, Kumla, Örebro, Sverige":"Byrsta, Kumla, Örebro, Rootsi","Skofteby, Härene, Västra Götaland, Sweden":"Skofteby, Västra Götaland, Rootsi","Ågård i Råda socken, Skaraborg län, Sverige":"Råda, Skaraborg, Rootsi"},"fi":{"1425–1514":"1425–1514","1420–1473":"1420–1473","1450–1485":"1450–1485","1405–1463":"1405–